We first prove the following theorem. 
\begin{Theorem}\label{thm:eqSF}
    The Pl\"ucker relations \eqref{eq:general-plucker} and the Laplace relations \eqref{eq:lap} generate the ideal $\calK[n-1]$ of the special fiber ring $\calF[n-1]$. In particular, $\calF[n-1]\isom \calF(I_2(\LL))$.
