Since “intrinsic geometries may vary from point to point,” a standard Vitali lemma cannot be applied directly; “comparability of the scaling factors is ensured” by the following comparability statement.
\begin{lemma}\label{la_comp_lem}
    Suppose $U(w), U(v)\in \mathcal{F}$ with $U(w)\cap U(v)\ne \emptyset$ and $l_w\le 2l_v$. Then for $\cc\ge 2$ defined in Lemma~\ref{p_decay_lem}, we have
