\label{th-main}
	Fix $R > 0$ sufficiently large such that $\phi(R) > \frac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{3}}$. The kink with the profile $\phi$ is orbitally stable in the NLS equation \begin{equation}
\label{NLS}
i \psi_t = \psi_{xx} - \psi + 4 |\psi|^2 \psi - 3 |\psi|^4 \psi.
\end{equation}
 with respect to perturbations  in $\mathcal{E} \cap \mathcal{H}_R$. To be precise, for every small $\epsilon > 0$ there is $\delta > 0$ such that if $\psi_0 \in \mathcal{E}$ satisfies  $\rho_R(\psi_0,\phi) \leq \delta^2$, then the unique solution $\psi \in C^0({\mathbb R},\mathcal{E})$ to the NLS equation (the equation above) with $\psi |_{t = 0} = \psi_0$ satisfies 
