\label{thm:connectedSum}
	Let $M^n$ be a closed aspherical manifold and $N$ a spin manifold. Assume that the rational strong Novikov conjecture holds for $\pi_1(M)$.
	Then the connected sum $M\# N$ does not carry any complete metric with positive scalar curvature. Furthermore, any complete metric with non-negative scalar curvature on $M\# N$ is Ricci-flat.

